abstract: Indonesian foreign official Hasan Kleib expresses concern over report that Australian authorities demolished boat carrying sixteen multinational migrants seeking asylum, and sent them back to sea in new vessel.
lead_paragraph: Australian officials then pushed the 16 migrants back to sea in another vessel, Indonesia said

headline.main: Indonesia: Australia Destroys Boat in Repelling Migrants, Official Says
headline.print_headline: Asia; Indonesia: Australia Destroys Boat in Repelling Migrants, Official Says
